## generalPurpose

General-purpose agent for researching complex questions, searching for code, and executing multi-step tasks.

## explore

Fast agent specialized for exploring codebases, supporting quick, medium, and very thorough exploration levels.

## shell

Command execution specialist for running bash commands, git operations, and other terminal tasks.

## browser-use

Browser automation specialist for performing UI interactions, web testing, and browser profiling.

## investigator

**Hunter-killer debug-and-fix specialist. Read-write.** Dispatched when `gate:full` fails at plan end. Receives a failure cluster (test suite + stack traces), investigates root cause, applies a targeted fix (max 3 attempts), and verifies. One investigator per failure cluster, dispatched in parallel. Reports STATUS: FIXED | PARTIAL | ESCALATE back to orchestrator. See `.cursor/agents/investigator.md`. Lead doc: [docs/leads/investigator.md](../../docs/leads/investigator.md).

**Not the research agent** — for read-only architectural investigation use the reviewer in research mode (dispatched by `/investigate` skill).

## planner-analyst

Pre-plan analysis agent for gathering codebase context before plan creation (`.cursor/agents/planner-analyst.md`).

## implementer

Implementation agent that executes tasks (`tg start` → work → `tg done`). Template at `.cursor/agents/implementer.md`.

## documenter

Documentation-only agent for tasks limited to markdown/docs (README, CHANGELOG, docs/). Template at `.cursor/agents/documenter.md`. Plan authors set `agent: documenter` for doc-only tasks.

## reviewer

**Two modes, always read-only.** (1) **PASS/FAIL mode** — quality-check sub-agent that evaluates implementations against specifications, called after an implementer completes a task. (2) **Research mode** — read-only investigation specialist used by the `/investigate` skill; receives a tactical directive and returns structured findings (files, function chains, schemas, API facades, suggested follow-up tasks). Template at `.cursor/agents/reviewer.md`.

## test-quality-auditor

Sub-agent that audits test quality and suggests improvements (`.cursor/agents/test-quality-auditor.md`).

## test-infra-mapper

Sub-agent that maps and documents test infrastructure (`.cursor/agents/test-infra-mapper.md`).

## test-coverage-scanner

Sub-agent that scans test coverage and highlights gaps (`.cursor/agents/test-coverage-scanner.md`).

## debugger

Systematic debugging sub-agent for hypothesis-driven investigation of **individual task-graph tasks**. Read-write. Operates inside the task graph (`tg start` → 4 phases → `tg done`), max 3 fix attempts before escalating via `tg note`. See `.cursor/agents/debugger.md`. Lead doc: [docs/leads/debug.md](../../docs/leads/debug.md).

**Not the same as investigator** — investigator is dispatched dynamically by the work skill when gate:full fails; debugger is assigned explicitly to a task in a plan.

## fixer

Escalation agent; resolves tasks after implementer/reviewer failure using a stronger model (inherits session model). See `.cursor/agents/fixer.md`.

## spec-reviewer

Spec compliance check sub-agent (PASS/FAIL). First stage of two-stage review. See `.cursor/agents/spec-reviewer.md`.

## quality-reviewer

Code quality check sub-agent (PASS/FAIL). Second stage of two-stage review. See `.cursor/agents/quality-reviewer.md`.

## reprioritise

**Orchestrator-direct (no sub-agents).** Read-write. Invoked when the user runs the reprioritise skill. Reviews active projects, answers "are these the right projects to be active?", produces a linear prioritised project list, and ensures at least 10 Ready (runnable) tasks by updating priority or activating tasks as needed. See `.cursor/skills/reprioritise/SKILL.md`. Lead doc: [docs/leads/reprioritise.md](../../docs/leads/reprioritise.md).

